    • averageStID

      public static double averageStID​(MesoStation station)
      obtains the average of the STID saved in a MesoStation object. The average is calculated by separating every character of the STID and casting it to it ASCII integer value
      Parameters:
      station - MesoStation that the average is going to be obtained
      Returns:
      return a double value of the average obtained from the ASCII value f each one of the caracted composing the STID

    • roundNumber

      public static int roundNumber​(double value)
      rounds a double number with the stated rule within this class. if the two digits after the decimal point a less than ROUNDING_LIMIT the rounding is done towards the floor, otherwise the rounding is done with the ceiling
      Parameters:
      value - value to be rounded
      Returns:
      the rounded integer

    • getFractionVal

      public static double getFractionVal​(double number, int sigFigs)
      it is utilized to obtain the fractional value of a double number at the given significant figures.
      Parameters:
      number - double number to which the fraction part is going to be removed
      sigFigs - number of significant figures to be taken from the double number. This number can only be positive
      Returns:
      the decimal portion of the original number with the amount of the desired significant figures

    • getFirstAvg

      public int[] getFirstAvg()
      Generates an array of integer populated with the ceiling , floor and rounded value of average of the station passed in the constructor
      Returns:
      returns an array of integers with the calculated first averages

    • calAverage

      public int calAverage()
      it calculates the final average between the rounded average obtained with the default station and the station passed in the constructor
      Specified by:
      calAverage in class MesoAsciiAbstract
      Returns:
      returns an integer value that is rounded differently than the roundNumber method. This method rounds the number depending if the calculated average has a fraction part or not. If the calculated average has a fraction part the return value would be the ceiling, otherwise it would be the floor

    • getFinalAvg

      public double getFinalAvg()
      Returns:
      returns the average of both averages, the one from the default station and the one from the station passed to the constructor
